cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the transmission of a secret message and proposes an achievable secrecy rate under a constraint on the equivocation rate at Eve. This is a core topic in information theory.
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with secure transmission in the presence of an eavesdropper and proposes a power and channel allocation algorithm to maximize the achievable secrecy rate. This is a core topic in cryptography and security.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with relay channels and proposes a power and channel allocation algorithm for resource allocation. This is a core topic in networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a power and channel allocation algorithm that maximizes the achievable secrecy rate by resorting to two coupled Gale-Shapley algorithms for stable matching problem. This is a core topic in systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the impact of discrete constellations and finite-length coding, which are important in multimedia applications such as image and video transmission.
